The paper focuses on conversational question answering, which involves understanding dialogue context and requires passage comprehension, coreference resolution, and contextual understanding. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the natural language processing (NLP) sub-category of computer science, which is cs.CL. Additionally, the paper proposes an innovated contextualized attention-based deep neural network, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.AI and cs.LG. The paper also leverages inter-attention and self-attention to comprehend conversation context, which could fall under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques to extract relevant information from the passage, which could suggest that it belongs to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
